lead_paragraph: An article on Thursday about Pete Buttigieg’s struggle to attract voters of color described incorrectly the votes cast in the 2016 Democratic caucuses in Elko County. There were 88 county delegates selected in the county, not 88 total votes recorded.

abstract: The party’s riskiest bet is now its likeliest.
snippet: The party’s riskiest bet is now its likeliest.
lead_paragraph: I’ve been enthusiastic about Mike Bloomberg’s race for president from its inception, partly on the theory that he was best positioned to rescue and represent the Democratic Party’s moderate wing. After Wednesday night’s debate debacle in Las Vegas, I’m starting to fear his candidacy might inadvertently destroy that wing — while wrecking the party’s chances in November.

abstract: The Iowa Democratic Party is agreeing to recount the results in about two dozen of almost 1,700 precinct caucuses as part of the ongoing process to resolve the weeks-long question of who won Iowa's tarnished presidential caucuses.
snippet: The Iowa Democratic Party is agreeing to recount the results in about two dozen of almost 1,700 precinct caucuses as part of the ongoing process to resolve the weeks-long question of who won Iowa's tarnished presidential caucuses.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — The Iowa Democratic Party is agreeing to recount the results in about two dozen of almost 1,700 precinct caucuses as part of the ongoing process to resolve the weeks-long question of who won Iowa's tarnished presidential caucuses.
headline_main: Iowa Democrats Agree to Buttigieg, Sanders Limited Recount
headline_print_headline: Iowa Democrats Agree to Buttigieg, Sanders Limited Recount

abstract: Candidates have hustled past tourists and slot machines to ask housekeepers and cooks for their votes in the back of flashy casinos. They've made their pitches over plates of tamales, tacos and soul food. They've walked a picket line in the street with union workers. And then, with unsurprising showmanship, there was that flock of pigeons with tiny MAGA hats.
snippet: Candidates have hustled past tourists and slot machines to ask housekeepers and cooks for their votes in the back of flashy casinos. They've made their pitches over plates of tamales, tacos and soul food. They've walked a picket line in the street...
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Candidates have hustled past tourists and slot machines to ask housekeepers and cooks for their votes in the back of flashy casinos. They've made their pitches over plates of tamales, tacos and soul food. They've walked a picket line in the street with union workers. And then, with unsurprising showmanship, there was that flock of pigeons with tiny MAGA hats.
headline_main: Picketing, Pigeons, Politics: Scenes From the Nevada Caucus
headline_print_headline: Picketing, Pigeons, Politics: Scenes From the Nevada Caucus

abstract: Just past the roulette wheel and slot machines, the smoky bars and blinking lights, Nevada Democrats are preparing to weigh in on their party's presidential nomination fight.

lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Just past the roulette wheel and slot machines, the smoky bars and blinking lights, Nevada Democrats are preparing to weigh in on their party's presidential nomination fight.
headline_main: Bright Lights, Big Stakes for Democrats in Nevada
headline_print_headline: Bright Lights, Big Stakes for Democrats in Nevada

abstract: Beyond the presidential candidates themselves, the Nevada caucuses Saturday will test Democratic National Committee Chairman Tom Perez as he tries to keep an already messy primary season from devolving into chaos.
snippet: Beyond the presidential candidates themselves, the Nevada caucuses Saturday will test Democratic National Committee Chairman Tom Perez as he tries to keep an already messy primary season from devolving into chaos.

headline_main: DNC Chair Unbowed by 2020 Fracas: 'My Job Is ... To Win'
